subSubSection.paragraph:
Foot in males 50.6–58.7 % ( x = 54.6 ± 2.6 ) SVL, 41.2–60.5 % ( x = 53.5 ± 10.7 ) in females; inner tarsal fold absent, series of conical tubercles along outer margin of tarsus; knee and heel bearing one conical tubercle each; tubercle on heel prominent; inner metatarsal tubercle oval, near three times length of elongated outer; supernumerary plantar tubercles numerous, rounded and low; subarticular tubercles rounded; toes bearing fleshy fringes along lateral margins; no webbing; disks on all toes, disks of toes II–V somewhat longer than wide, but smaller than those of fingers; Toe V longer that Toe III; tip of Toe V does not reach distal subarticular tubercle of toe IV (condition B;
Lynch and Duellman 1997
).

Distribution. Known from Valle de Sibundoy in Colón, San Francisco and Sibundoy municipalities at elevations of 2200–2750 m . (
Fig. 3
).
